transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling, this is John, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi, yes, this is Mr. Romo, I'm calling to discontinue the CD medication.

Speaker 1: Okay, I need your name again and your zip code.

Speaker 2: John Romo, R-O-M-O, 92410.

Speaker 1: 1010 Terrace Road?

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: Okay, I can do that for you, sir, but if I do cancel this out, it would close it out entirely,

Speaker 2: because your prescription would then be canceled.

Speaker 1: It may not be ordered again down the road.

Speaker 2: Would you prefer I pause it for you so you don't have to get it as often?

Speaker 1: Well, as I said, I just went to my mailbox and received this other one.

Speaker 2: I haven't even used the first one.

Speaker 1: I mean, my workouts don't come, my opportunities don't come quite often,

Speaker 2: like when they did the last time, it wasn't ready.

Speaker 1: So it's like, you know, now I've got two bottles of 10, I guess, or 12.

Speaker 2: I don't know how much it says.

Speaker 1: There's 10 in the one that came today.

Speaker 2: Ten, yeah.

Speaker 1: Yeah, and there was 10 in the other one before, and I still have those.

Speaker 2: I haven't even opened it yet.

Speaker 1: Okay, so you're fine with just canceling out the prescription then?

Speaker 2: Yeah, just canceling out, because if for some reason I get more whatever,

Speaker 1: I'll go ahead and start all over again.

Speaker 2: Okay, I'm taking care of that for you, John.

Speaker 1: All right, thanks a lot.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
